Source: North Otago Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: To facilitate the creation of poor men's diggings, the Government might issue instructions to resident magistrates to provide <i>bona fide</i> applicants .. with miner's rights and such tools as are necessary, together with free rations for a few months, and an extended claim as a reward in case of the discovery of a poor man's gold field capable of carrying a population of 2000 men.
